{
  "texts": [
    "This protocol ensures consistency, reduces bias, and enhances the transparency and reproducibility of the review.",
    "The search phase aims to identify relevant papers using search strategies, snowballing, or a hybrid approach.",
    "Search strategies are typically implemented by creating a query based on a combination of terms using boolean operators (Team 2007; Glanville et al. 2019).",
    "This query is then executed on designated search engines.",
    "In snowballing, the researcher examines the references and citations of an initial group of papers (also known as seed papers) to identify additional articles."
  ]
}